MEP Engineer - PT Leighton Contractors Indonesia
MEP Engineer  -
MEP Engineer
Responsibilities
To coordinate MEP (mechanical, electrical and plumbing) work activities of the project area to which he has been assigned according to agreed plan, while maintaining a health & safe working environment  with the prime objective of ensuring that  daily, weekly and monthly production targets are achieved.  Diploma in civil /structural engineering or related disciplines ;Deep knowledge upon practical application of mechanical/electrical/plumbing installation & safety legal requirements ;Experience in High Rise Building Projects ;4 – 7 years experience in civil/construction ;Have extensive experience in MEP installation works with a capability in monitoring direct staff and subcontractors ;Experience in managing operational and technical role in the construction industry ;Experience working at civil contractor is preferred ;Intermediate knowledge of MEP design software/hardware skills ;Basic skills on project management software ;Basic knowledge of civil operation regulatory requirement ;Basic skills on MS-Word, and Excel ;Strong quantitative and numeric skills ;Proficient in English ;Indonesian citizen.
